Hey I’m working on an old HubSpot site and it has this script being loaded, which I’m not familiar with. It generates a 404, but is clearly a HubSpot script as it uses the portal ID in the filename.

&lt;!-- Start of Messages Async Embed --&gt;
  &lt;script type=“text/javascript”&gt;
    (function(d, s, id) {
      if (d.getElementById(id)){ return; }
      var js = d.createElement(s); js.src = ‘<https://api.usemessages.com/messages/v1/embed/xxxxxx.js>’; js.id = id;
      e = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0]; e.parentNode.insertBefore(js, e);
      })(document, ‘script’, ‘messages-xxxxxx’)
   &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;!-- End of Messages Async Embed --&gt;

Is this some old element that just needs removed? I can’t find reference anywhere as to what this is for.
